asset.author: PFI Western Wear Store
asset.hookText:
http://PFIWestern.com - Come out to the farm in Halltown, MO to see a real-world (and real funny!) test of the Walls Waterproof Duck Coats and Overalls!
Join Paul, Roy Whitehead from Walls and the Halltown Fire Department as they hose down PFI's Boot Manager, Ron, to see how the waterproof coat and overalls perform! 
Because they are made of Nylon, the Walls "Water Pruf" shell technology has half the weight, but twice the strength as traditional cotton duck. Lightweight, stain resistant, waterproof and windproof, these western work clothes are perfect for hunting, motorcycle riding, bucking hay on the farm or anything else you want to try in them!
